Former cricketer V.V.S. Laxman inaugurated the MaxCure Advanced Orthopaedic & Joint Replacement Centre on the hospital premises here at Madhapur on Wednesday.The centre led by experienced orthopaedicsâ€™ team is equipped with advanced infrastructure to handle all kinds of simple to complex orthopaedic conditions, including sports medicine and trauma injuries, said Anil Krishna, MD, MaxCure Hospitals.The real strength of the facility is its super specialist team which adopts a multi-disciplinary approach to handle trauma and other complex conditions, he added.MaxCure has the distinction of being one of the very few sub-specialty based orthopaedic chains with seamless connectivity across AP and Telangana integrating all its centres in Madhapur, Secretariat, Karimnagar, Nizamabad and Nellore.